ction = <!-- location of awards page or section --> }} '''Lin Yuxin''' (born 10 October 2000) is a Chinese [[amateur golf|amateur]] [[golf]]er.
Aged 17, he qualified directly for both the [[2018 Masters Tournament|2018 Masters]] and the [[2018 Open Championship]] as the 2017 [[Asia-Pacific Amateur Championship|Asia-Pacific Amateur champion]].<ref name="Aug18">{{cite news |url=http://www.augusta.com/masters/players/bios/Yuxin_Lin.shtml |title=Yuxin Lin |newspaper=The Augusta Chronicle |date=2018 |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref> Playing in the first two rounds of the 2018 Masters at [[Augusta National Golf Club|Augusta]], Lin scored 79 and 80 for [[par (score)|15-over-par]], which meant he [[cut (golf)|missed the cut]] and did not qualify for the last two rounds.<ref name="Aug18"/> In the 2018 Open Championship at [[Carnoustie Golf Links|Carnoustie]], he scored 80 and 74 for 12-over-par in the first two rounds, again missing the cut.<ref name="Open18">{{cite web |url=https://www.theopen.com/Leaderboard#!/traditional |title=2018 Open – Leaderboard |work=The Open |publisher=R&A |date=2018 |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref>
Lin was the first winner of the Asia-Pacific to receive a direct invitation to both the Masters and The Open Championship. Previously the winner had received an invitation to the Masters but it was only starting in 2018 that the winner also had an automatic Open entry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theopen.com/News/News/2017/01/Winner-of-Asia-Pacific-Amateur-Championship-to-earn-exemption-into-The-Open |title=Winner of Asia Pacific Amateur Championship to earn exemption into The Open |work=The Open |publisher=R&A |date=18 January 2017 |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/golf/columns/story?columnist=harig_bob&id=3909740 |title=Masters, R&A open doors for amateurs |work=ESPN |date=18 January 2017 |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://wagr.randa.org/default.sps?pagegid={72A1781A-C8FD-44DF-9DA1-2B03400FFF27}&pcpageid=22039 |title=World Amateur Golf Ranking – Frequently Asked Questions |publisher=R&A/USGA | date=2018 | accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.golfdigest.com/story/fantastic-finish-gives-chinas-lin-yuxin-the-asia-pacific-amateur-title-spots-in-masters-british-open |title=Fantastic finish gives China's Lin Yuxin the Asia-Pacific Amateur title, spots in Masters, British Open |last=Herrington |first=Ryan |magazine=Golf Digest |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/sport/china/article/2117651/china-golf-prodigy-lin-yuxin-returns-clearwater-bay-open-after-securing |title=Young Master: China golf prodigy Lin secures Augusta spot |newspaper=South China Morning Post |accessdate=29 July 2018}}</ref>
