{{Infobox officeholder |name = İsmail Hakki Akansel |office = [[Mayor of Istanbul]] |image = |predecessor = [[Aytekin Kotil]] |successor = [[Ecmel Kutay]] |party = |birth_date = 1924 |birth_place = [[Erzincan]], Turkey<ref>{{cite web|title=İsmail Hakkı Akansel|url=http://www.biyografya.com/biyografi/10049|website=Biyografya|accessdate=8 August 2017|language=tr}}</ref> |death_date = May 15, 2016 (aged 92) |death_place = |otherparty = |spouse = |alma_mater = |profession = |religion = |term_start = September 12, 1980 |term_end = August 30, 1981 }}
'''İsmail Hakki Akansel''' (1924 – May 15, 2016) was a Turkish military general and politician. In 1980, Akansel was appointed [[Mayor of Istanbul]] following the [[1980 Turkish coup d'état]] and the establishment of military rule in [[Turkey]]. He served as the Mayor of Istanbul from September 1980 to August 1981.<ref name=hab>{{cite news |first= |last= |title=Emekli Orgeneral İsmail Hakkı Akansel, İzmir'de Vefat Etti |url=http://www.haberler.com/emekli-orgeneral-ismail-hakki-akansel-izmir-de-8446602-haberi/ |work=Haberler.com |date=2016-05-17 |accessdate=2016-06-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160622102346/http://www.haberler.com/emekli-orgeneral-ismail-hakki-akansel-izmir-de-8446602-haberi/ |archivedate=2016-06-22 |df= }}</ref><ref name=hurriyet>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Emekli Orgeneral İsmail Hakkı Akansel, İzmir'de vefat etti |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/yerel-haberler/izmir-haberleri/emekli-orgeneral-ismail-hakki-akansel-izmir-de_281783/ |work=[[Hurriyet]] |date=2016-05-17 |accessdate=2016-06-12}}</ref>
He retired from the military in 1985.<ref name=hurriyet/>
İsmail Hakki Akansel died in [[Izmir]], Turkey, on May 15, 2016, at the age of 92.<ref name=hab/><ref name=hurriyet/> He was buried in Istanbul.<ref name=hab/>
